    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn SpaceVim, I have a key binding `SPC b c` to clear other written buffer, after type this key binding, the tabline does not redraw.\r\n\r\nthe key binding is mapped to this function:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction! SpaceVim#mapping#clear_saved_buffers() abort\r\n  call s:BUFFER.filter_do(\r\n        \\ {\r\n          \\ 'expr' : [\r\n            \\ 'buflisted(v:val)',\r\n            \\ 'index(tabpagebuflist(), v:val) == -1',\r\n            \\ 'getbufvar(v:val, \"&mod\") == 0',\r\n            \\ ],\r\n            \\ 'do' : 'noautocmd bd %d'\r\n            \\ }\r\n            \\ )\r\nendfunction\r\n```\r\n\r\nmaybe this is because I use `noautocmd` to run `bd` command.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nvim foo fzz bff\r\n\r\ntype `SPC b c`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe tabline should be updated, and only current buffer is listed.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWin11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nneovim-qt\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nempty\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop repo",
