            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "It seems a bit tricky, but I'll try to keep it simple.\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. Create the file `tabline.lua`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nfunction _G.render_tabline()\r\n  local result = ''\r\n  local current_buffer = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\r\n  for _, number in ipairs(vim.api.nvim_list_bufs()) do\r\n    if vim.bo[number].buflisted == true then\r\n      local highlight = number == current_buffer and '%#TabLineSel#' or '%#TabLine#'\r\n      local path = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(number)\r\n      result = result .. highlight .. ' ' .. path .. ' '\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n  result = result .. '%#TabLineFill#'\r\n  return result\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.opt.tabline = '%!v:lua._G.render_tabline()'\r\nvim.opt.showtabline = 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Create a couple of files:\r\n\r\n`touch a.txt b.txt`\r\n\r\n3. Run neovim:\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean -u tabline.lua a.txt b.txt`\r\n\r\n4. You can see the tabline is displaying the two aforementioned files\r\n5. Delete one of the buffers (not current buffer):\r\n`:bdelete b.txt`\r\n6. You can see the tabline is still displaying the two buffers",
